methods.addSeries:
Add the given series to this MultiSeries

:param series: (MultiSeriesInternal.T) - series
:param key: (java.lang.Object) - key used to determine the name of the series
methods.applyTransform:
Calls a .update() on the underlying table with the given formula: underlyingTable.update(columnName = update)

:param columnName: (java.lang.String) - the resulting column
:param update: (java.lang.String) - the formula inside
:param classesToImport: (java.lang.Class[]) - classes to import into the query scope
:param params: (java.util.Map<java.lang.String,java.lang.Object>) - parameters to add to the query scope
:param columnTypesPreserved: (boolean) - set to true if the update clause is 'add only' with respect to columns. This allows
        the copying of ACLs

Gets the chart on which this data will be plotted.

methods.copy:
Create a copy of the series on a different set of axes.

:param axes: (io.deephaven.plot.AxesImpl) - new axes.

methods.createSeries:
Creates a new series for this multi-series.

*Overload 1*  
  :param seriesName: (java.lang.String) - name for the series
  :param t: (io.deephaven.engine.table.impl.BaseTable) - client side source table
  :return: (MultiSeriesInternal.T) new series for this multi-series
  
*Overload 2*  
  :param seriesName: (java.lang.String) - name for the series
  :param t: (io.deephaven.engine.table.impl.BaseTable) - client side source table
  :param dynamicSeriesNamer: (io.deephaven.plot.datasets.DynamicSeriesNamer) - creates the name for the newly generated series. Ensures unique names.
  :return: (MultiSeriesInternal.T) new series for this multi-series
